cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze and compare documents written by unknown authors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval and similarity measurement, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a type of computational model, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
